<section>
  <p class="intro">Buttons are a fairly ubiquitous element around the web, however there are some very special requirements for using them. For example, did you know that any clickable element that produces some kind of interactive behavior and isn't a hyperlink is <b>required</b> to be a <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> to meet accessibility standards? It's true!</p>
  <p class="intro">This can make <code>&lt;button&gt;</code>s an extremely important part of your app, so why not use a convenient, totally rad component-ized version that meets accessibility requirements, is visually customizable, and supports DDAU behavior?</p>
</section>
